The paper discusses a process of representing existing legacy systems in terms of models, which is a common topic in software engineering (cs.SE). The focus is on maintainer scripts, which are executable code snippets used to finalize package configuration, indicating a possible connection to programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of meta-models, which are commonly used in deep learning (cs.DL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with complex software systems that evolve rapidly and independently, which could be considered a systems and control topic (cs.SY).
